      "text": "This is where ‘grant funded’ finally finds its place, and bites hard. In DaO, Robin chose - something of a slip, in a politics of **production** - to frame the ‘four economies’ in terms of their funding, rather than the relations of *production* under which their practice is organised, and the altered, prefigurative relations of production of a ‘new’ economy. The mutual sector was thus easily misrecognised as a minority NGO sector or ‘the third sector’ of the Big Society (‘the mixed economy’), rather than as the **entire**, enormous cultural, economic and aesthetic force of global civil society, and ‘the world’s largest movement’ of blessed unrest. \n"
